</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Farmer, Philip Jose (1983), "Author's Introduction" to: <i><a href="/wiki/River_of_Eternity" title="River of Eternity">River of Eternity</a></i>; <a href="/wiki/Huntington_Woods,_Michigan" title="Huntington Woods, Michigan">Huntington Woods, Michigan</a>: <a href="/wiki/Phantasia_Press" title="Phantasia Press">Phantasia Press</a>, pp i-x.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The 1966 magazine version was about 12,000 words. The final "definitive" version is about 33,750 words.  (See Farmer's "Forward" in <i>Riverworld and Other Stories</i> (1979); New York: Berkley Books, pp 3-5.) This story depicts the unhappy afterlife of a completely human <a href="/wiki/Jesus_Christ" class="mw-redirect" title="Jesus Christ">Jesus Christ</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-WWE-1972-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-WWE-1972_4-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1972">"1972 Award Winners &amp; Nominees"</a>. <i>Worlds Without End</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2009-10-05</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Worlds+Without+End&amp;rft.atitle=1972+Award+Winners+%26+Nominees&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldswithoutend.com%2Fbooks_year_index.asp%3Fyear%3D1972&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARiverworld" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.isfdb.org/cgi-bin/pl.cgi?34352">"Publication: Tales of Riverworld"</a>. <i>www.isfdb.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2022-06-26</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.isfdb.org&amp;rft.atitle=Publication%3A+Tales+of+Riverworld&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.isfdb.org%2Fcgi-bin%2Fpl.cgi%3F34352&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARiverworld" class="Z3988"></span></span>
